LondonJOHN McEnroe, known for his on-court outbursts, would be in his element at next month's Wimbledon tennis tournament, where every fist-pump of elation and cry of angst will be analysed by artificial intelligence (AI) to compile video highlights.The All England Lawn Tennis Club and its technology partner IBM said the Watson AI platform had been taught to recognise players' emotions, which it would combine with an analysis of crowd noise, players' movements and match data.IBM's client executive for Wimbledon Sam Seddon said that the company was using machine learning to trying to find those seconds when players had a heightened sense of emotion after an exciting shot or rally."If you've got the visual element from the player, and you know that it's a tight pressure point in the match, then those are the points that you are going to really target at in the highlights package," he said in an interview.


